        "id": "r_easy_1",
        "category": "Information and Ideas",
        "skill": "Central Ideas and Details",
        "text": "To dye wool, Navajo (Din\u00e9) weaver Lillie Taylor uses plants and vegetables from Arizona, where she lives. For example, she achieved the deep reds and browns featured in her 2003 rug In the Path of the Four Seasons by using Arizona dock roots, drying and grinding them before mixing the powder with water to create a dye bath. To intensify the appearance of certain colors, Taylor also sometimes mixes in clay obtained from nearby soil.\n\nWhich choice best states the main idea of the text?",
        "choices": [
          "Reds and browns are not commonly featured in most of Taylor's rugs.",
          "In the Path of the Four Seasons is widely acclaimed for its many colors and innovative weaving techniques.",
          "Taylor draws on local resources in the approach she uses to dye wool.",
          "Taylor finds it difficult to locate Arizona dock root in the desert."
        ],
        "correct": 2
      },
      {
        "id": "r_easy_2",
        "category": "Craft and Structure",
        "skill": "Words in Context",
        "text": "In recommending Bao Phi's collection S\u00f4ng I Sing, a librarian noted that pieces by the spoken-word poet don't lose their ______ nature when printed: the language has the same pleasant musical quality on the page as it does when performed by Phi.\n\nWhich choice completes the text with the most logical and precise word or phrase?",
        "choices": [
          "jarring",
          "scholarly",
          "melodic",
          "personal"
        ],
        "correct": 2
      },
      {
        "id": "r_easy_3",
        "category": "Craft and Structure",
        "skill": "Words in Context",
        "text": "The work of molecular biophysicist Enrique M. De La Cruz is known for ______ traditional boundaries between academic disciplines. The university laboratory that De La Cruz runs includes engineers, biologists, chemists, and physicists, and the research the lab produces makes use of insights and techniques from all those fields.\n\nWhich choice completes the text with the most logical and precise word or phrase?",
        "choices": [
          "reinforcing",
          "anticipating",
          "epitomizing",
          "transcending"
        ],
        "correct": 3
      },
      {
        "id": "r_easy_4",
        "category": "Information and Ideas",
        "skill": "Central Ideas",
        "text": "Scientists have discovered that certain plants can absorb heavy metals from contaminated soil. This process, called phytoremediation, offers a natural and cost-effective way to clean polluted areas. Researchers are now working to identify which plant species are most effective at removing specific toxins.\n\nWhat is the main purpose of the text?",
        "choices": [
          "To explain how plants become contaminated with heavy metals",
          "To describe a natural method of cleaning polluted soil",
          "To argue that phytoremediation is more expensive than other methods",
          "To list all plants capable of absorbing toxins"
        ],
        "correct": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "r_easy_5",
        "category": "Craft and Structure",
        "skill": "Words in Context",
        "text": "The archaeologist's discovery of ancient pottery fragments was particularly ______ because the pieces revealed previously unknown trading patterns between distant civilizations.\n\nWhich choice completes the text with the most logical and precise word or phrase?",
        "choices": [
          "insignificant",
          "revealing",
          "confusing",
          "typical"
        ],
        "correct": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "r_easy_6",
        "category": "Information and Ideas",
        "skill": "Central Ideas",
        "text": "The invention of the printing press in the 15th century revolutionized the spread of information. Before this technology, books had to be copied by hand, making them expensive and rare. With the printing press, books could be produced quickly and affordably, allowing knowledge to reach a much wider audience.\n\nWhich choice best describes the main idea of the text?",
        "choices": [
          "Books were always expensive before the 15th century.",
          "The printing press made books more accessible to people.",
          "Hand-copied books were more beautiful than printed books.",
          "Knowledge was secret before the printing press was invented."
        ],
        "correct": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "r_easy_7",
        "category": "Expression of Ideas",
        "skill": "Transitions",
        "text": "Solar panels convert sunlight into electricity. ______, wind turbines generate power from moving air. Both technologies provide renewable energy sources that don't produce greenhouse gases.\n\nWhich choice completes the text with the most logical transition?",
        "choices": [
          "However",
          "Similarly",
          "Therefore",
          "Nevertheless"
        ],
        "correct": 1
