      {
        "id": "r_easy_10",
        "category": "Information and Ideas",
        "skill": "Inferences",
        "text": "Local farmers have reported increased crop yields this year. Weather conditions have been ideal, with adequate rainfall and moderate temperatures throughout the growing season. Additionally, many farmers have adopted new irrigation techniques.\n\nBased on the text, which inference is most supported?",
        "choices": [
          "Farmers will always have good yields in the future.",
          "Weather and farming methods both contributed to higher yields.",
          "New irrigation techniques are unnecessary when rainfall is adequate.",
          "All farmers in every location had increased yields."
        ],
        "correct": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "r_easy_11",
        "category": "Information and Ideas",
        "skill": "Central Ideas",
        "text": "Bees play a crucial role in agriculture by pollinating crops. Without bees, many fruits, vegetables, and nuts would not be able to reproduce. Scientists estimate that one-third of the food we eat depends on pollination by bees and other insects.\n\nWhat is the main point of the text?",
        "choices": [
          "Bees are the only insects that pollinate crops.",
          "Bees are essential for producing much of our food supply.",
          "One-third of all food comes from bee products like honey.",
          "Scientists study bees more than any other insect."
        ],
        "correct": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "r_easy_12",
        "category": "Craft and Structure",
        "skill": "Words in Context",
        "text": "The chef's ______ attention to detail ensured that every dish was perfectly prepared and beautifully presented.\n\nWhich choice completes the text with the most logical and precise word or phrase?",
        "choices": [
          "careless",
          "meticulous",
          "random",
