        "id": "r_med_1",
        "category": "Information and Ideas",
        "skill": "Command of Evidence",
        "text": "Jan Gimsa, Robert Sleigh, and Ulrike Gimsa have hypothesized that the sail-like structure running down the back of the dinosaur Spinosaurus aegyptiacus improved the animal's success in underwater pursuits of prey species capable of making quick, evasive movements. To evaluate their hypothesis, a second team of researchers constructed two battery-powered mechanical models of S. aegyptiacus, one with a sail and one without, and subjected the models to a series of identical tests in a water-filled tank.\n\nWhich finding from the model tests, if true, would most strongly support Gimsa and colleagues' hypothesis?",
        "choices": [
          "The model with a sail took significantly longer to travel a specified distance while submerged than the model without a sail did.",
          "The model with a sail displaced significantly more water while submerged than the model without a sail did.",
          "The model with a sail had significantly less battery power remaining after completing the tests than the model without a sail did.",
          "The model with a sail took significantly less time to complete a sharp turn while submerged than the model without a sail did."
        ],
        "correct": 3
      },
      {
        "id": "r_med_2",
        "category": "Information and Ideas",
        "skill": "Command of Evidence",
        "text": "\"Ghosts of the Old Year\" is an early 1900s poem by James Weldon Johnson. In the poem, the speaker describes experiencing an ongoing cycle of anticipation followed by regretful reflection.\n\nWhich quotation from \"Ghosts of the Old Year\" most effectively illustrates the claim?",
        "choices": [
          "\"The snow has ceased its fluttering flight, / The wind sunk to a whisper light, / An ominous stillness fills the night, / A pause\u2014a hush.\"",
          "\"And so the years go swiftly by, / Each, coming, brings ambitions high, / And each, departing, leaves a sigh / Linked to the past.\"",
          "\"What does this brazen tongue declare, / That falling on the midnight air / Brings to my heart a sense of care / Akin to fright?\"",
          "\"It tells of many a squandered day, / Of slighted gems and treasured clay, / Of precious stores not laid away, / Of fields unreaped.\""
        ],
        "correct": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "r_med_3",
        "category": "Information and Ideas",
        "skill": "Inferences",
        "text": "Many animals, including humans, must sleep, and sleep is known to have a role in everything from healing injuries to encoding information in long-term memory. But some scientists claim that, from an evolutionary standpoint, deep sleep for hours at a time leaves an animal so vulnerable that the known benefits of sleeping seem insufficient to explain why it became so widespread in the animal kingdom. These scientists therefore imply that ______\n\nWhich choice most logically completes the text?",
        "choices": [
          "it is more important to understand how widespread prolonged deep sleep is than to understand its function.",
          "prolonged deep sleep is likely advantageous in ways that have yet to be discovered.",
          "many traits that provide significant benefits for an animal also likely pose risks to that animal.",
          "most traits perform functions that are hard to understand from an evolutionary standpoint."
        ],
        "correct": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "r_med_4",
        "category": "Craft and Structure",
        "skill": "Cross-Text Connections",
        "text": "Text 1: Historians have traditionally attributed the decline of the Roman Empire primarily to military defeats and economic problems.\n\nText 2: Recent archaeological findings suggest that environmental factors, including climate change and disease outbreaks, played a more significant role in Rome's decline than previously thought. Evidence shows widespread crop failures and population decline due to plague.\n\nBased on the texts, how would the author of Text 2 most likely respond to Text 1?",
        "choices": [
          "By agreeing that military and economic factors were the only causes",
          "By suggesting that environmental factors should also be considered",
          "By arguing that historians have completely misunderstood Rome's decline",
          "By dismissing the importance of archaeological evidence"
        ],
        "correct": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "r_med_5",
        "category": "Expression of Ideas",
        "skill": "Rhetorical Synthesis",
        "text": "While researching ocean conservation, a student found the following information:\n\n\u2022 Coral reefs cover less than 1% of the ocean floor\n\u2022 They provide habitat for approximately 25% of all marine species\n\u2022 Coral reefs protect coastlines from storm damage and erosion\n\u2022 They support fishing industries that feed millions of people\n\nThe student wants to emphasize the disproportionate importance of coral reefs. Which choice most effectively uses information from the notes to accomplish this goal?",
        "choices": [
          "Coral reefs protect coastlines and support fishing industries around the world.",
          "Although coral reefs cover less than 1% of the ocean floor, they provide habitat for about 25% of marine species.",
          "Coral reefs support fishing industries that provide food for millions of people globally.",
          "Approximately 25% of all marine species live in coral reef habitats."
        ],
        "correct": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "r_med_6",
        "category": "Standard English Conventions",
        "skill": "Form and Structure",
        "text": "Researchers studying animal behavior have observed ______ some species demonstrate remarkably complex problem-solving abilities.\n\nWhich choice completes the text so that it conforms to the conventions of Standard English?",
        "choices": [
          "that:",
          "that",
          "that;",
          "that,"
        ],
        "correct": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "r_med_7",
        "category": "Craft and Structure",
        "skill": "Text Structure",
        "text": "The invention of the microscope in the early 17th century opened up an entirely new world of scientific discovery. For the first time, scientists could observe cells, bacteria, and other microscopic organisms. This breakthrough led to advances in medicine, biology, and our understanding of disease.\n\nWhich choice best describes the function of the underlined sentence in the text?",
        "choices": [
          "It contradicts the claim made in the previous sentence.",
          "It provides specific examples of what scientists could now observe.",
          "It explains why the microscope was difficult to invent.",
          "It introduces a new topic unrelated to the invention of the microscope."
        ],
        "correct": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "r_med_8",
        "category": "Expression of Ideas",
        "skill": "Transitions",
        "text": "The Amazon rainforest produces approximately 20% of Earth's oxygen. ______, it is often called \"the lungs of the planet.\"\n\nWhich choice completes the text with the most logical transition?",
        "choices": [
