      {
        "id": "r_med_13",
        "category": "Expression of Ideas",
        "skill": "Rhetorical Synthesis",
        "text": "While researching renewable energy, a student noted:\n\n\u2022 Wind turbines can generate electricity for 25+ years\n\u2022 Solar panels typically last 20-30 years\n\u2022 Both technologies require minimal maintenance\n\u2022 Initial installation costs have decreased significantly\n\nThe student wants to emphasize the long-term viability of renewable energy. Which choice most effectively accomplishes this goal?",
        "choices": [
          "Solar panels and wind turbines both require minimal maintenance after installation.",
          "Installation costs for renewable energy technologies have decreased in recent years.",
          "Renewable energy technologies like solar panels and wind turbines can generate power for decades with minimal maintenance.",
          "Wind turbines generate electricity for over 25 years."
        ],
        "correct": 2
      },
      {
        "id": "r_med_14",
        "category": "Information and Ideas",
        "skill": "Command of Evidence",
        "text": "A team of researchers studied the impact of urban green spaces on community health. Their findings suggested that neighborhoods with more parks and gardens had lower rates of certain health issues.\n\nWhich finding, if true, would most strongly support this conclusion?",
        "choices": [
