      {
        "id": "r_med_16",
        "category": "Craft and Structure",
        "skill": "Text Structure",
        "text": "Photosynthesis is the process by which plants convert sunlight into chemical energy. Chlorophyll, the green pigment in plant cells, captures light energy. This energy is then used to transform carbon dioxide and water into glucose and oxygen.\n\nWhat is the primary function of the second sentence?",
