    {
      "id": "passage_7",
      "difficulty": "easy",
      "category": "Social Science",
      "title": "Benefits of Reading",
      "source": "Educational research",
      "text": "Reading regularly provides numerous cognitive and emotional benefits. Studies show that people who read frequently have larger vocabularies, better comprehension skills, and improved ability to understand complex ideas. Reading also exercises the brain, potentially reducing the risk of cognitive decline as we age.\n\nBeyond intellectual benefits, reading offers emotional and social advantages. Fiction readers often demonstrate greater empathy and understanding of others' perspectives, as they regularly engage with diverse characters and situations. Reading can also reduce stress, provide entertainment, and offer opportunities for learning about different cultures and experiences.",
